Episodes.Title: Birds of a Feather
Episodes.Plot: A young boy wants to hire Harry because he believes that monsters are after him and his mom. Harry doesn't want to take the kid's money, but he also knows from his own experience that a child's monsters are often all too real.
Episodes.GuestStars: Natalie Lisinska,  Daniel Kash,  Earl Pastko,  Heather Hanson,  Jonathan Higgins,  Matthew Knight,  Dylan Everett,  Deborah Odell,  Marie Ward

Episodes.Title: The Boone Identity
Episodes.Plot: A grieving father asks Harry to help put his daughter's spirit to rest. This should be easy. All Dresden has to do is track down the killer and make sure that justice has been done. There's only one catch: the killer died only hours after the murder.
Episodes.GuestStars: John Robinson,  Judy Marshak,  Domenic Cuzzocrea,  Tom Barnett,  Kaleigh Nevin,  C. David Johnson,  Kevin Rushton

Episodes.Title: Hair of the Dog
Episodes.Plot: A series of ritualistic murders starts to look a lot like werewolves so Harry, of course, gets dragged in. Thing is, it looks like the lycanthropes aren't the killers... they're the victims.
Episodes.GuestStars: Derwin Phillips,  Krista Bridges,  Ipsita Paul,  Kathleen Munroe,  Kyra Harper,  Constantine Alex Karzis

Episodes.Title: Rules of Engagement
Episodes.Plot: A beautiful young woman asks Harry to help her recover some stolen money. Before long, Dresden discovers a connection between this case and a dark, supernatural evil, and that his lovely client has been hiding something.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kim Coates,  Meredith Henderson,  Corey Sevier,  Chapelle Jaffe

Episodes.Title: Bad Blood
Episodes.Plot: After a failed hit on her life, Bianca, Chicago's most powerful vampire, calls upon Harry Dresden.  In debt to her for saving his life years before, he agrees to help her find the mastermind behind the plan to take her down.
Episodes.GuestStars: Simon Northwood,  Michael Copeman,  Lyriq Bent,  Layton Morrison,  Laura Vandervoort,  Kent Staines,  Joanne Kelly,  Jane McLean

Episodes.Title: Soul Beneficiary
Episodes.Plot: An otherwise healthy man experiencing premonitions of his own demise seeks Harry's help but ends up croaking right in his office. As the dark circumstances surrounding his death are revealed, Harry finds himself in the crosshairs of a dangerous magic-user; meanwhile, the crime that got Bob condemned to living in his own skull for all eternity finally comes to light.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kerry Lai Fatt,  Paul Sun-Hyung Lee,  Louise Nicol,  Hamish McEwan,  Tara Rosling,  Karen Cliche

Episodes.Title: Walls
Episodes.Plot: Harry investigates the death of a college student which leads him to a most unusual ring of thieves.  A group of students is using magick to commit a series of impossible thefts, and Harry must stop them quickly.  Not only because what they are doing is wrong, but also because the magick will eventually kill them all.
Episodes.GuestStars: Odeen  Eccleston,  Steve Byers,  Kerry Dorey,  Nathan Stephenson,  Tyrone Savage

Episodes.Title: Storm Front
Episodes.Plot: We are introduced to Harry Dresden, private detective and practicing wizard.  When he tries to help the Chicago Police Department solve a grisly murder, he finds himself the target of a homicidal magician.  And as if that isn't bad enough, the High Council of wizards begins to think that he is falling to the dark side, so he must elude them as well.  Now he must stop the murderer and clear his name before his time runs out.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jennifer Kydd,  Elizabeth Thai,  Rebecca McFarland,  John DeSantis,  Greg Bryk,  Christine Tizzard,  Jonathan Whittaker,  Daniel Kash,  Raoul Bhaneja,  Sherry Miller,  Shannon Boodram,  Joanne Kelly

Episodes.Title: The Other Dick
Episodes.Plot: When Chicago PI Jim Brennan is murdered by supernatural means, Harry must team up with Brennan's assistant to find the murderer.
Episodes.GuestStars: Richard Blackburn,  Claudia Black,  John Boylan,  Chris Owens,  Stephanie Moore,  Lara Kelly,  Craig Brown

Episodes.Title: What About Bob?
Episodes.Plot: Things seem to be going well between Harry and his new flame until she walks out on him... and takes Bob's skull.  Now Dresden must find Bob and rescue him from the clutches of an old enemy.  But will Bob want to be rescued?
Episodes.GuestStars: Jordan Madley,  Raoul Bhaneja,  Matthew Knight,  Jonathan Higgins,  Conrad Coates,  Daniel Kash

Episodes.Title: Things That Go Bump
Episodes.Plot: Morgan and Ancient Mai must come to Harry for protection and shelter from powerful enemies of Mai's.  They make it to the relative safety of Dresden's place, but suddenly find that they are all trapped by a powerful spell.  Now Harry must work with them to find a way out before the spell turns deadly.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jane McLean,  James Binkley,  Conrad Coates,  Jonathan Higgins,  Bobby Del Rio,  Christine Horne

Episodes.Title: Second City
Episodes.Plot: Dresden and Murphy must work together to solve the mystery of a former gang member who drowns on dry land, miles from the nearest lake. Meanwhile, Murphy's father is in town, and he doesn't have a very high opinion of his daughter's freelance consultant.
Episodes.GuestStars: Cheryl Quiacos,  Chuck Shamata,  Dan Petronijevic,  Bill Lake,  Yannick Bisson,  Chad Camilleri,  Raoul Bhaneja
